## 3. Code Changes Required

### 3.1 Function Changes

#### Old (Ollama): `generate_response(prompt)`
- Direct HTTP requests to localhost:11434
- Custom error handling with fallbacks to legacy endpoints
- No official SDK

#### New (Groq): `generate_response(prompt)`
- Uses official Groq Python SDK
- Cleaner API, built-in retry mechanisms
- Streaming support (can be enabled)
- Consistent response format

### 3.2 Key API Differences

| Aspect | Ollama | Groq |
|--------|--------|------|
| Authentication | None (local) | Bearer token (GROQ_API_KEY) |
| Model | Any local model | Predefined models |
| Response Format | `{"choices": [{"message": {"content": "..."}}]}` | Same (OpenAI-compatible) |
| Error Handling | HTTP errors, timeouts | Rate limits (429), API errors |
| Rate Limits | None (local) | Yes - monitor usage |
| Cost | Infrastructure (GPU) | Per token |
| Latency | Variable (local) | ~200-500ms (cloud) |

